										</titlePart>
									</title>
								</textBody>
								<ipcEntry edition="19800101" kind="4" symbol="G02F0001135000" ipcLevel="C" entryType="K" isRenumbered="N" isDead="N" lang="EN" noadvanced="yes">
									<textBody><title>
											<titlePart><text>Liquid crystal cells structurally associated with a supplementary layer, e.g. a photoconducting or a ferro-electric layer, the properties of which can be electrically or optically varied</text>
											</titlePart>
										</title>
									</textBody>
								</ipcEntry>
							</ipcEntry>
							<ipcEntry edition="19800101" kind="3" symbol="G02F0001137000" ipcLevel="C" entryType="K" isRenumbered="N" isDead="N" lang="EN" noadvanced="yes">
								<textBody><title>
										<titlePart><text>characterised by a particular electro- or magneto-optical effect, e.g. field-induced phase transition, orientation effect, guest-host interaction, dynamic scattering</text>
										</titlePart>
									</title>
								</textBody>
							</ipcEntry>
						</ipcEntry>
						<ipcEntry edition="19740701" kind="2" symbol="G02F0001170000" ipcLevel="C" entryType="K" isRenumbered="N" isDead="N" lang="EN" noadvanced="yes">
							<textBody><title>
									<titlePart><text>by using variable absorption devices</text>
										<entryReference><mref ref="G02F0001015000" endRef="G02F0001137000" refType="/" endRefType="/" refLevel="c" endRefLevel="c"></mref> take precedence</entryReference>
									</titlePart>
								</title>
							</textBody>
						</ipcEntry>
						<ipcEntry edition="19740701" kind="2" symbol="G02F0001190000" ipcLevel="C" entryType="K" isRenumbered="N" isDead="N" lang="EN" noadvanced="yes">
							<textBody><title>
									<titlePart><text>by using variable reflection or refraction</text>
